---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import DbArchitecture from '../components/DbArchitecture';
---

<Base title="Database Design" active="db-schema" section="architecture" description="Interactive schema for the podcast-factory SQLite database — 16 SOLID-compliant tables spanning the pipeline, knowledge library, and Kashkole corpus layer.">
  <header class="page-hero">
    <div class="page-hero-inner">
      <span class="eyebrow">Database design</span>
      <h1 class="page-hero-title">What the database manages and why.</h1>
      <p class="page-hero-lede">
        Sixteen SOLID-compliant tables replacing scattered JSONL and JSON files across pipeline books and external corpora.
        One SQLite database consolidates the knowledge store, etymology layer, corpus provenance, topic taxonomy,
        cost tracking, episode registry, and quality audit trail — everything queryable and cross-book for the first time.
        The Kashkole corpus tables make the intelligence library the central hub that enriches every future book production.
      </p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="stack">
    <DbArchitecture client:load />
  </section>

  <section class="stack design-notes">
    <h2>Design decisions</h2>
    <div class="grid-3">
      <div class="card stack">
        <span class="eyebrow">Why SQLite, not a server?</span>
        <p>
          The factory runs on a single machine. SQLite has no daemon, no config,
          no connection pooling — just a file. It handles the pipeline's write pattern
          (one book at a time, one phase at a time) without any overhead.
          The knowledge base, cost ledger, and episode registry can all be queried
          with plain <code>SELECT</code> statements from any script.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card stack">
        <span class="eyebrow">Etymology at every scale</span>
        <p>
          Three tables form the etymology spine: <strong>arabic_roots</strong> holds
          every Semitic root with its pre-computed abjad sum; <strong>word_etymologies</strong>
          maps each root to its morphological derivations with semantic nuances and
          esoteric notes per word; <strong>letter_profiles</strong> is a static 28-row
          table that drives teaching depth at the letter level — makhraj, sifāt, solar/lunar,
          Quranic frequency, and Sufi colour correspondences. Join all three in one query.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card stack">
        <span class="eyebrow">SOLID/DRY foundation from day one</span>
        <p>
          Four design rules are baked in. <strong>atom_sources</strong> unifies all provenance
          (pipeline books and Kashkole chapters) in one table with a <code>source_type</code>
          discriminator and a CHECK constraint — no polymorphic NULL ambiguity.
          <strong>topic_type_taxonomy</strong> replaces a hard-coded driver dict with 18 seed rows
          that the ingestion driver JOINs instead of duplicating.
          <strong>atom_topic_tags</strong> is a proper covering-indexed join table replacing
          a file-based tag index. And <code>needs_review</code> on every atom surfaces
          WARN-verdict quality signals without a separate table.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  /* ── Component root ─────────────────────────────────────────── */
  :global(.dba-root) {
    font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif;
  }

  /* ── Filter bar ─────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  :global(.dba-filters) {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--sp-2);
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-5);
  }
  :global(.dba-filter-label) {
    font-size: var(--fs-sm);
    color: var(--c-ink-muted);
    margin-right: var(--sp-1);
  }
  :global(.dba-pill) {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 6px;
    padding: 5px 12px;
    border-radius: 999px;
    border: 1.5px solid var(--c-rule);
    background: transparent;
    font: 600 12px 'Lato', sans-serif;
    color: var(--c-ink-dim);
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: border-color 0.15s, background 0.15s, color 0.15s;
  }
  :global(.dba-pill:hover) {
    border-color: var(--c-ink-muted);
    color: var(--c-ink);
  }
  :global(.dba-pill--active) {
    border-color: var(--pill-color, var(--c-accent));
    background: color-mix(in oklab, var(--pill-color, var(--c-accent)) 8%, white);
    color: var(--pill-color, var(--c-accent));
  }
  :global(.dba-pill--clear) {
    border-color: var(--c-ink-muted);
    color: var(--c-ink-dim);
  }
  :global(.dba-pill-dot) {
    width: 8px;
    height: 8px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    background: var(--cat-color, #87827a);
  }

  /* ── Main layout ─────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  :global(.dba-layout) {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: var(--sp-6);
    align-items: start;
  }
  :global(.dba-layout--split) {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
  }
  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    :global(.dba-layout--split) {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }

  /* ── SVG diagram ─────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  :global(.dba-diagram-wrap) {
    border: 1px solid var(--c-rule);
    border-radius: var(--r-lg);
    background: var(--c-bg-card);
    padding: var(--sp-3) var(--sp-3) var(--sp-2);
    overflow: hidden;
    max-width: 440px;  /* constrain SVG to near-natural size so font-size CSS px don't over-scale */
  }
  :global(.dba-svg) {
    width: 100%;
    display: block;
  }
  /* SVG text classes — CSS px values, do NOT scale with SVG viewBox transform */
  :global(.dba-tbl-name) {
    font: 700 14px 'Lato', sans-serif;
    fill: var(--c-ink);
    transition: fill 0.18s;
  }
  :global(.dba-tbl-count) {
    font: 12px 'Lato', sans-serif;
    fill: var(--c-ink-muted);
    transition: fill 0.18s;
  }
  :global(.dba-edge-lbl) {
    font: 700 11px 'Lato', sans-serif;
    fill: var(--c-ink-muted);
  }
  /* SVG transition helpers — CSS classes so transitions live in CSS, not inline */
  :global(.dba-edge)   { transition: stroke 0.2s, stroke-width 0.2s; }
  :global(.dba-node-g) { cursor: pointer; }
  :global(.dba-box)    { transition: all 0.18s; }
  :global(.dba-fill)   { transition: fill 0.18s; }
  :global(.dba-legend-svg) { vertical-align: middle; }
  :global(.dba-diagram-legend) {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--sp-3) var(--sp-5);
    padding: var(--sp-2) var(--sp-2) 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--c-rule);
    margin-top: var(--sp-2);
  }
  :global(.dba-legend-item) {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 6px;
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--c-ink-muted);
  }
  :global(.dba-legend-dot) {
    width: 10px;
    height: 10px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--cat-color, var(--c-rule));
  }
  :global(.dba-hint) {
    margin-left: auto;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* ── Detail panel ────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  :global(.dba-panel) {
    border: 1px solid var(--c-rule);
    border-radius: var(--r-lg);
    background: var(--c-bg-card);
    padding: var(--sp-5);
    overflow-y: auto;
    max-height: 580px;
    animation: panel-in 0.18s ease;
  }
  @keyframes panel-in {
    from { opacity: 0; transform: translateX(8px); }
    to   { opacity: 1; transform: translateX(0); }
  }
  :global(.dba-panel--empty) {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: var(--sp-3);
    text-align: center;
    color: var(--c-ink-dim);
    font-size: var(--fs-sm);
    min-height: 300px;
  }
  :global(.dba-empty-icon) {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    opacity: 0.2;
  }
  :global(.dba-empty-hint) {
    color: var(--c-ink-muted);
    font-size: 12px;
  }

  /* Panel header */
  :global(.dba-panel-header) {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--sp-2);
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-4);
  }
  :global(.dba-panel-name) {
    font: 700 22px 'Source Serif 4', Georgia, serif;
    color: var(--c-ink);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--cat-color, var(--c-accent));
    padding-left: var(--sp-3);
    line-height: 1.2;
  }
  :global(.dba-panel-badges) {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--sp-2);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  :global(.dba-badge) {
    font: 600 11px 'Lato', sans-serif;
    padding: 3px 9px;
    border-radius: 999px;
    background: var(--cat-bg, var(--c-bg-sunken));
    color: var(--cat-color, var(--c-ink));
  }
  :global(.dba-badge--wave) { background: var(--c-bg); color: var(--c-ink-muted); border: 1px solid var(--c-rule); }
  :global(.dba-badge--wave1) { color: var(--c-green); border-color: var(--c-green); background: rgba(74,124,74,0.06); }
  :global(.dba-badge--wave2) { color: #0078d4; border-color: #0078d4; background: rgba(0,120,212,0.06); }
  :global(.dba-badge--wave3) { color: var(--c-ink-muted); }

  /* Purpose text */
  :global(.dba-panel-purpose) {
    font-size: var(--fs-sm);
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--c-ink-dim);
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-4);
    padding: var(--sp-3);
    background: var(--c-bg);
    border-radius: var(--r-md);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--c-rule);
  }

  /* Phase chips */
  :global(.dba-phase-grid) {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--sp-4);
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-4);
  }
  :global(.dba-phase-label) {
    font: 700 10px 'Lato', sans-serif;
    color: var(--c-ink-muted);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.07em;
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-2);
  }
  :global(.dba-phase-chips) {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--sp-1);
  }
  :global(.dba-chip) {
    font: 600 10.5px 'Lato', sans-serif;
    padding: 3px 8px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    border: none;
  }
  :global(.dba-chip--write) { background: rgba(139,69,19,0.08); color: #8b4513; }
  :global(.dba-chip--read)  { background: rgba(0,120,212,0.08); color: #0078d4; }
  :global(.dba-chip--related) {
    background: transparent;
    border: 1.5px solid var(--cat-color, var(--c-rule));
    color: var(--cat-color, var(--c-ink));
    cursor: pointer;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 4px;
    transition: background 0.15s;
  }
  :global(.dba-chip--related:hover) { opacity: 0.75; }
  :global(.dba-chip-type) { opacity: 0.6; font-weight: 400; }

  /* Related tables */
  :global(.dba-related) { margin-bottom: var(--sp-4); }
  :global(.dba-related-chips) { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: var(--sp-2); margin-top: var(--sp-2); }

  /* Section label */
  :global(.dba-section-label) {
    font: 700 10px 'Lato', sans-serif;
    color: var(--c-ink-muted);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.07em;
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-2);
  }
  :global(.dba-section-label--mt) { margin-top: 1rem; }

  /* Fields */
  :global(.dba-fields) {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 2px;
  }
  :global(.dba-field) {
    padding: var(--sp-2) var(--sp-3);
    border-radius: var(--r-md);
    border: 1px solid transparent;
    transition: background 0.1s;
  }
  :global(.dba-field:hover) { background: var(--c-bg); border-color: var(--c-rule); }
  :global(.dba-field--pk) { border-color: rgba(184,134,11,0.25); background: rgba(184,134,11,0.04); }
  :global(.dba-field-top) {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: var(--sp-2);
    margin-bottom: 3px;
  }
  :global(.dba-field-name) {
    font: 700 12px 'Lato', monospace;
    color: var(--c-ink);
    font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
  }
  :global(.dba-field-tags) { display: flex; gap: 4px; flex-shrink: 0; }
  :global(.dba-tag) {
    font: 600 9.5px 'Lato', sans-serif;
    padding: 1px 6px;
    border-radius: 3px;
  }
  :global(.dba-tag--type) { background: var(--c-bg); color: var(--c-ink-dim); border: 1px solid var(--c-rule); }
  :global(.dba-tag--pk)   { background: rgba(184,134,11,0.12); color: #b8860b; }
  :global(.dba-tag--fk)   { background: rgba(0,120,212,0.10); color: #0078d4; }
  :global(.dba-tag--null) { background: var(--c-bg); color: var(--c-ink-muted); border: 1px dashed var(--c-rule); }
  :global(.dba-field-desc) {
    font-size: 11.5px;
    color: var(--c-ink-dim);
    line-height: 1.45;
    margin: 0;
  }
  :global(.dba-field-fk-label) {
    font: 10px 'Lato', monospace;
    color: #0078d4;
    margin: 2px 0 0;
    font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
  }

  /* Design notes */
  .design-notes h2 { margin-bottom: var(--sp-4); }
  .design-notes p  { font-size: var(--fs-sm); line-height: 1.6; color: var(--c-ink-dim); margin: 0; }
  .design-notes code { font-size: 11px; background: var(--c-bg); padding: 1px 4px; border-radius: 3px; }
</style>
